How to add levels:
every list that starts with CHARTS:: can be edited (not chart::)
each element in the list is a level, the same items in different lists are still the same level (for example, the first element in each list is part of the same level)

start at bpms and bpmTiles, the number first used in bpmTiles is how many beats before the song starts (as a negative number), and the number in bpms is the bpm (beats per minute) of the song.

CHARTS::angles stores all the level tiles, as the angles in degrees, so straight tile is 180, left/right bends are 90 and 270, 
some angles don't have the costumes for them, so they won't display correctly, but they should work in gameplay. you can create your own costume or just wait for an update.

CHARTS::swirls just stores swirls, the numbers is each tile that has a swirl. note that this does not change the timing, it changes the direction tiles after it go, so for example an angle of 90 will always be short, regardless of the direction it acutally goes. this means that you should either ignore how the chart looks while writing angles, or always write swirls when you reach them.

CHARTS::midspins stores midspins, works like swirls. the graphics for midspin tiles don't actually exist yet though.

other than the first part of bpms and bpmTiles, the bpms stores the bpm changes for the song (is used to speedup / slowdown), and the bpmTiles stores which tiles the bpm changes happen.

to add the actual songs, add them to the gameplay sprite, with the number being the level name. MAKE SURE THERE'S NO SILENCE AT THE START. songs will be out of sync if there's silence at the start, since you'll hear the song start late. if you can, add some clicks to the start as a countin, make sure it acutally matches the beat of the song.
you can edit the song countin with decimals to try and compensate for silence, but you should try to avoid this, because then you'll need to change it every time you edit the song bpm, and it'll make syncing up the song a nightmare.
i reccomend editing the audio with audacity, make sure tto disable snapping at the bottom, and export as mp3.

camera rotation can be done in the decor sprite, i plan to make this sprite handle all decoration in the future

a blank level in CHARTS::angles ends the game, and will return to the menu when it's added.
